objects.name: Money Libra
objects.description: Money Libra is a cloud threat actor group that uses the name Kinsing as the directory location for a family of cryptocurrency mining malware and supporting initialization files. The group has begun to expand their operations outside of Docker containers and have begun to specifically target container and cloud credential files contained on compromised cloud workloads.

objects.name: Campaign 2 - Leveraging Log4j to gain CSP credentials
objects.description: Money Libra has been reported to have leveraged the Log4j, Log4Shell, vulnerability CVE-2021-44228 upon which to illicit the retreival of sensitive cloud service platform access and secret keys from compromised cloud instances. This information directly targets the cloud service platform and indicates that Money Libra operators are attempting to gain initial access to an organizations cloud platform.

objects.name: Campaign 1 - Cryptomining Operations
objects.description: This cryptojacking operation targets exposed Docker Daemon APIs using GoLang based malicious processes running on Ubuntu containers. The attack progresses through the following kill chain operations: initial access, evasion, persistence, lateral movement, and culminates with the payload of a crypto miner called 'kdevtmptfsi'.
